<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>President Truman’s speech on April 4 at the ceremony for the signing
                                of the Atlantic Pact contained a statement designed to endorse and
                                emphasize recent statements by the Secretary of State on Iran, as
                                well as on Greece and Turkey; for text, see circular telegram of
                                April 2, <ref target="frus1949v04#pg_270">volume IV, page
                                270</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>